.TH "adjust_lpt_heap" 9 "adjust_lpt_heap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
adjust_lpt_heap \- move a changed heap entry up or down the heap.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" adjust_lpt_heap
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct ubifs_lpt_heap *heap "  ","
.BI "struct ubifs_lprops *lprops "  ","
.BI "int hpos "  ","
.BI "int cat "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "heap" 12
LEB category heap
.IP "lprops" 12
LEB properties to move
.IP "hpos" 12
heap position of \fIlprops\fP
.IP "cat" 12
LEB category
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Changed entries in a heap are moved up or down until the parent's value is
greater.  In the case of LPT's category heaps, the value is either the amount
of free space or the amount of dirty space, depending on the category.
